UC1: Execute Press-on-Loss in Advanced Areas
Primary Actor: Outfield Agents
Goal: Regain possession quickly while maintaining defensive structure
Trigger: 
•	Loss of possession in the attacking third
Preconditions: 
•	Team is in organised attacking shape
•	Sufficient stamina available
Main Flow:
1.	Nearest agent applies immediate pressure to the ball carrier.
2.	Surrounding agents block nearby passing lanes rather than engaging directly.
3.	A temporary pressing cage is formed to delay progression.
Conditional Triggers:
•	Lateral pass near the touchline
•	Poor first touch by opponent
•	Opponent receives ball with back to goal
•	Goalkeeper receives a back pass
Postconditions:
•	Defensive shape is preserved
•	Stamina expenditure is reduced
•	Exposure to counter-attacks is minimized

UC2: Exploit Set Pieces as High-Impact Scoring Opportunities
Primary Actor: Set-Piece Coordinator Agent
Goal: Increase goal output from repeatable dead-ball situations
Trigger:
•	Award of a corner, free kick, or attacking throw-in
Preconditions:
•	Set-piece routine assigned
•	Player roles predefined
Main Flow:
1.	Team transitions into structured set-piece formation.
2.	Predefined movement patterns are executed.
3.	Delivery is targeted based on prior match analysis.
Postconditions:
•	Increased shot quality from set plays
•	Improved conversion from controlled situations

UC3: Perform Predictive Goalkeeper Shot-Stopping
Primary Actor: Goalkeeper Agent
Goal: Improve save probability through optimal positioning
Trigger:
•	Opponent enters shooting range
Preconditions:
•	Ball carrier identified
•	Shot angle calculable
Main Flow:
1.	Goalkeeper estimates probable shot direction.
2.	Position is adjusted based on shooting angle and probability.
3.	Save action is executed accordingly.
Postconditions:
•	Improved coverage of central and acute-angle shots

UC4: Act as Sweeper Keeper During Build-Up
Primary Actor: Goalkeeper Agent
Goal: Improve build-up stability under pressure
Trigger:
•	Team in possession under high press
Preconditions:
•	No immediate shooting threat
•	Passing lanes available
Main Flow:
1.	Goalkeeper moves into supporting outfield position.
2.	Acts as additional passing option.
3.	Distributes ball to relieve pressure or switch play.
Constraints:
•	Situational rules prevent high-risk positioning
Postconditions:
•	Fewer forced long clearances
Improved press resistance

UC5: Apply 4-2-3-1 Formation to Exploit Single Pivot Midfield
Primary Actor: Tactical Controller
Goal: Destabilise Helios’ 4-3-3 structure
Trigger:
•	Match start or tactical reset
Preconditions:
•	Opponent using single-pivot midfield
Main Flow:
1.	Team adopts 4-2-3-1 formation.
2.	Double pivot blocks central lanes.
3.	Wide positioning forces opposition width.
Postconditions:
•	Central progression restricted
•	Improved defensive stability

UC6: Execute Asymmetric Double Pivot Roles
Primary Actor: Defensive Midfield Agents
Goal: Disrupt opponent midfield balance
Trigger:
•	Controlled possession in midfield
Main Flow:
1.	One pivot maintains screening role.
2.	Second pivot advances to progress play.
3.	Opponent’s single pivot is drawn out of position.
Postconditions:
•	Central space exposed
•	Improved vertical progression

UC7: Maintain Rest Defence During Attacks
Primary Actor: Defensive Unit
Goal: Prevent immediate vertical counter-attacks
Trigger:
•	Team enters attacking phase
Preconditions:
•	Possession established
Main Flow:
1.	Minimum of three players remain behind the ball.
2.	Central lanes are protected.
3.	Counter-attacks are delayed or neutralised.
Postconditions:
•	Reduced counter-attacking threat
Faster defensive recovery

UC8: Enable Adaptive Behaviour of the Number 10
Primary Actor: Attacking Midfielder Agent
Goal: Introduce uncertainty into defensive decision-making
Trigger:
•	Sustained possession in attacking third
Main Flow:
1.	Agent evaluates defensive structure.
2.	Selects one of the following behaviours:
o	Drop deeper as a false 10
o	Advance into the box as a secondary striker
o	Drift into half-spaces to overload wide areas
Postconditions:
•	Defensive marking disrupted
Increased chance creation

UC9: Create Scoring Opportunities via Cutbacks
Primary Actor: Wide and Central Attacking Agents
Goal: Exploit Helios’ defensive retreat behaviour
Trigger:
•	Wide player reaches advanced wide area
Main Flow:
1.	Wide agent attacks the byline.
2.	Central agents delay box entry.
3.	Cutback is delivered to late-arriving runners.
Postconditions:
•	Higher-quality shooting opportunities
•	Improved goal conversion

UC10: Generate Match Statistics and Performance Visualisations
Primary Actor: Analyst / Evaluation Module
Secondary Actor: Coach / Developer
Goal:
Collect match performance data and generate graphical summaries to evaluate tactical effectiveness against Helios.
Trigger
•	End of match
•	Manual evaluation request
Preconditions
•	Match has been completed
•	Event data has been logged (passes, shots, possession, turnovers, etc.)
Main Flow
1.	System extracts key match statistics from the simulation logs.
2.	Metrics are aggregated across defined phases of play.
3.	Statistical summaries are generated (e.g. averages, totals, ratios).
4.	Visual representations are produced, such as:
o	Possession percentage over time
o	Shot locations and xG heatmaps
o	Goals conceded from counter-attacks
o	Pressing recoveries in final third
o	Set-piece goals and chances created
5.	Graphs are exported for analysis and reporting.
Postconditions
•	Performance trends are observable
•	Tactical changes can be quantitatively evaluated
•	Results can be compared across multiple matches
Outputs
•	Line graphs
•	Bar charts
•	Heatmaps
•	Match summary tables
